    {
      "content": "Resource authoring checklist",
      "pos": [
        2,
        30
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This checklist is a list of best practices when authoring a new DSC Resource",
      "pos": [
        31,
        107
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource module contains .psd1 file and schema.mof for every resource",
      "pos": [
        111,
        180
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The first thing you should do is to check that your resource has correct structure and contains all required files.",
      "pos": [
        182,
        297
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Every resource module should contain a .psd1 file and every non-composite resource should have schema.mof file.",
      "pos": [
        298,
        409
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resources that do not contain schema will not be listed by <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get-DscResource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and users will not be able to use the intellisense when writing code against those modules in ISE.",
      "pos": [
        410,
        587
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The sample directory structure for xRemoteFile resource, which is part of the xPSDesiredStateConfiguration resource module, could look as follows:",
      "pos": [
        589,
        735
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource and schema are correct and have been verified using DscResourceDesigner cmdlets",
      "pos": [
        1093,
        1181
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Another important aspect is verifying the resource schema (*.schema.mof) file.",
      "pos": [
        1185,
        1263
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure that:",
      "pos": [
        1265,
        1280
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Property types are correct (e.g. don’t use String for properties which accept numeric values, you should use UInt32 or other numeric types instead)",
      "pos": [
        1285,
        1432
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Property attributes are specified correctly ([key], [required], [write], [read])",
      "pos": [
        1437,
        1517
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At least one parameter in the schema has to be marked as [key]",
      "pos": [
        1522,
        1584
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "[read] property cannot coexist together with any of: [required], [key], [write]",
      "pos": [
        1589,
        1668
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If multiple qualifiers are specified except [read], then [key] takes precedence",
      "pos": [
        1673,
        1752
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If [write] and [required] are specified, then [required] takes precedence",
      "pos": [
        1753,
        1826
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "ValueMap is specified where appropriate",
      "pos": [
        1831,
        1870
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Example:",
      "pos": [
        1872,
        1880
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Friendly name is specified and confirms to DSC naming conventions",
      "pos": [
        2043,
        2108
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Example:",
      "pos": [
        2110,
        2118
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Every field has meaningful description",
      "pos": [
        2186,
        2224
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Below you can find a good example of the resource schema file (this is the actual schema of xRemoteFile resource from the DSC Resource Kit)",
      "pos": [
        2226,
        2365
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3244,
        3402
      ],
      "content": "Additionally, you should use <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Test-xDscResource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Test-xDscSchema<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> cmdlets from Dsc Resource Designer to automatically verify the resource and schema:"
    },
    {
      "content": "For example:",
      "pos": [
        3494,
        3506
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource loads without errors",
      "pos": [
        3657,
        3686
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once you verified that resource contains all necessary files and verified them using DSC Resource Designer, it’s time to check whether resource module can be successfully loaded.",
      "pos": [
        3690,
        3868
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can do it either manually, by running <ph id=\"ph1\">`Import-Module &lt;resource_module&gt; -force `</ph> and confirming that no errors occurred, or by writing test automation.",
      "pos": [
        3869,
        4023
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In case of the latter, you can follow this structure in your test case:",
      "pos": [
        4024,
        4095
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "4   Resource is idempotent in the positive case",
      "pos": [
        4267,
        4314
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "One of the fundamental characteristics of every DSC resource should be idempotence.",
      "pos": [
        4316,
        4399
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It means that we can apply a DSC configuration containing that resource multiple times without changing the result beyond the initial application.",
      "pos": [
        4400,
        4546
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, if we create a configuration which contains the following File resource:",
      "pos": [
        4547,
        4632
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After applying it for the first time, file test.txt should appear in C:\\test folder.",
      "pos": [
        4736,
        4820
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, subsequent runs of the same configuration should not change the state of the machine (e.g. no copies of the test.txt file should be created).",
      "pos": [
        4821,
        4971
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To ensure our resource is idempotent we can repeatedly call <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Set-TargetResource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> when testing the resource directly, or call <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> multiple times when doing end to end testing.",
      "pos": [
        4972,
        5171
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The result should be the same after every run.",
      "pos": [
        5172,
        5218
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "User modification scenario was tested",
      "pos": [
        5225,
        5262
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "User modification is another common scenario worth testing out.",
      "pos": [
        5266,
        5329
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It helps you verify that <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Set-TargetResource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Test-TargetResource<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> function properly.",
      "pos": [
        5330,
        5424
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Here are steps you should take to test it:",
      "pos": [
        5425,
        5467
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Start with the resource not in the desired state.",
      "pos": [
        5472,
        5521
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Run configuration with your resource",
      "pos": [
        5526,
        5562
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5567,
        5612
      ],
      "content": "Verify <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Test-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> returns True"
    },
    {
      "content": "Modify the resource out of the desired state",
      "pos": [
        5617,
        5661
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Verify <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Test-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> returns false",
      "pos": [
        5666,
        5712
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Here’s a more concrete example using Registry resource:",
      "pos": [
        5713,
        5768
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Start with registry key not in the desired state",
      "pos": [
        5773,
        5821
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5826,
        5930
      ],
      "content": "Run <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> with a configuration to put it in the desired state and verify it passes."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5935,
        5991
      ],
      "content": "Run <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Test-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and verify it returns true"
    },
    {
      "content": "Modify the value of the key so that it is not in the desired state",
      "pos": [
        5996,
        6062
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6067,
        6124
      ],
      "content": "Run <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Test-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and verify it returns false"
    },
    {
      "content": "Get-TargetResource functionality was verified using Get-DscConfiguration",
      "pos": [
        6129,
        6201
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Get-TargetResource should return details of the current state of the resource.",
      "pos": [
        6203,
        6281
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure you test it by calling Get-DscConfiguration after you apply the configuration and verifying that output correctly reflects the current state of the machine.",
      "pos": [
        6282,
        6448
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's important to test it separately, since any issues in this area won't appear when calling Start-DscConfiguration.",
      "pos": [
        6449,
        6566
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6571,
        6654
      ],
      "content": "Resource was verified by calling <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get/Set/Test-TargetResource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> functions directly"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6659,
        6819
      ],
      "content": "Make sure you test the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get/Set/Test-TargetResource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> functions implemented in your resource by calling them directly and verifying that they work as expected."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6824,
        6889
      ],
      "content": "Resource was verified End to End using <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>"
    },
    {
      "content": "Testing <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get/Set/Test-TargetResource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> functions by calling them directly is important, but not all issues will be discovered this way.",
      "pos": [
        6894,
        7030
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should focus significant part of your testing on using <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> or the pull server.",
      "pos": [
        7031,
        7136
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In fact, this is how users will use the resource, so don’t underestimate the significance of this type of tests.",
      "pos": [
        7137,
        7249
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Possible types of issues:",
      "pos": [
        7251,
        7276
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Credential/Session may behave differently because the DSC agent runs as a service.",
      "pos": [
        7281,
        7363
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Be sure to test any features here end to end.",
      "pos": [
        7365,
        7410
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Verify error messages displayed by the resource make sense.",
      "pos": [
        7415,
        7474
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, errors outputted by <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> may be different than those displayed when calling the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Set-TargetResource<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> function directly.",
      "pos": [
        7475,
        7631
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource behaves correctly on all DSC supported platforms (or returns a specific error otherwise)",
      "pos": [
        7636,
        7733
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource should work on all DSC supported platforms (Windows Server 2008 R2 and newer).",
      "pos": [
        7737,
        7824
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure you install latest WMF (Windows Management Framework) on your OS to get the latest version of DSC.",
      "pos": [
        7825,
        7933
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If resource by-design does not work on some of these platforms, a specific error message should be returned.",
      "pos": [
        7934,
        8042
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Also, make sure your resource checks whether cmdlets you are calling are present on particular machine.",
      "pos": [
        8043,
        8146
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Windows Server 2012 added a large number of new cmdlets that are not available on Windows Server 2008R2, even with WMF installed.",
      "pos": [
        8147,
        8276
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource functionality was verified on Windows Client (if applicable)",
      "pos": [
        8282,
        8351
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "One very common test gap is verifying the resource only on server versions of Windows.",
      "pos": [
        8355,
        8441
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Many resources are also designed to work on Client SKUs, so if that’s true in your case, don’t forget to test it on those platforms as well.",
      "pos": [
        8442,
        8582
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Get-DSCResource lists the resource",
      "pos": [
        8587,
        8621
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After deploying the module on the machine, calling Get-DscResource should list your resource among others as a result.",
      "pos": [
        8625,
        8743
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you can’t find your resource in the list, make sure that schema.mof file for that resource exists.",
      "pos": [
        8744,
        8845
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource module contains examples",
      "pos": [
        8850,
        8883
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you intend to share the resource (which you hopefully do), creating quality examples which will help others understand how to use it.",
      "pos": [
        8887,
        9023
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is crucial, especially since many users treat sample code as documentation.",
      "pos": [
        9024,
        9104
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "First, you should determine the examples that will be included with the module – at minimum, you should cover most important use cases for your resource:",
      "pos": [
        9110,
        9263
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If your module contains several resources that need to work together for an end-to-end scenario, the basic end-to-end example would ideally be first.",
      "pos": [
        9268,
        9417
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The initial examples should be very simple -- how to get started with your resources in small manageable chunks (e.g. creating a new VHD)",
      "pos": [
        9422,
        9559
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Subsequent examples should build on those examples (e.g. creating a VM from a VHD, removing VM, modifying VM), and show advanced functionality (e.g. creating a VM with dynamic memory)",
      "pos": [
        9564,
        9747
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Example configurations should be parameterized (all values should be passed to the configuration as parameters and there should be no hardcoded values):",
      "pos": [
        9752,
        9904
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It’s a good practice to include (commented out) example of how to call the configuration with the actual values at the end of the example script.",
      "pos": [
        10621,
        10766
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, in the configuration above it won’t be obvious for everyone that the best way to specify UserAgent is:",
      "pos": [
        10768,
        10883
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "That’s why we should include comment with sample execution of the configuration:",
      "pos": [
        10963,
        11043
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For each example, write a short description which explains what it does, and the meaning of the parameters.",
      "pos": [
        11501,
        11608
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure examples cover most the important scenarios for your resource and if there’s nothing missing, verify that they all execute and put machine in the desired state.",
      "pos": [
        11614,
        11784
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Error messages are easy to understand and help users solve problems",
      "pos": [
        11791,
        11858
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Good error messages should be:",
      "pos": [
        11862,
        11892
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There: The biggest problem with error messages is that they often don’t exist, so make sure they are there.",
      "pos": [
        11897,
        12004
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Easy to understand: Human readable, no obscure error codes",
      "pos": [
        12010,
        12068
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Precise: Describe what’s exactly the problem",
      "pos": [
        12073,
        12117
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Constructive: Advice how to fix the issue",
      "pos": [
        12122,
        12163
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Polite: Don’t blame user or make them feel stupid",
      "pos": [
        12168,
        12217
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure you verify errors in End to End scenarios (using <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>), because they may differ from those returned when running resource functions directly.",
      "pos": [
        12218,
        12391
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Log messages are easy to understand and informative (including –verbose, –debug and ETW logs)",
      "pos": [
        12397,
        12490
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensure that logs outputted by the resource are easy to understand and provide value to the user.",
      "pos": [
        12494,
        12590
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resources should output all information which might be helpful to the user, but more logs is not always better.",
      "pos": [
        12591,
        12702
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should avoid redundancy and outputting data which does not provide additional value – don’t make someone go through hundreds of log entries in order to find what they're looking for.",
      "pos": [
        12703,
        12889
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Of course, no logs is not an acceptable solution for this problem either.",
      "pos": [
        12890,
        12963
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When testing, you should also analyze verbose and debug logs (by running <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start-DscConfiguration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> with –verbose and –debug switches appropriately), as well as ETW logs.",
      "pos": [
        12966,
        13136
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To see DSC ETW logs, go to Event Viewer and open the following folder: Applications and Services- Microsoft - Windows - Desired State Configuration.",
      "pos": [
        13137,
        13285
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By default there will be Operational channel, but make sure you enable Analytic and Debug channels (you have to do it before running the configuration).",
      "pos": [
        13287,
        13439
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To enable Analytic/Debug channels, you can execute script below:",
      "pos": [
        13441,
        13505
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource implementation does not contain hardcoded paths",
      "pos": [
        13996,
        14052
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensure there are no hardcoded paths in the resource implementation, particularly if they assume language (en-us), or when there are system variables that can be used.",
      "pos": [
        14056,
        14222
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If your resource need to access specific paths, use environment variables instead of hardcoding the path, as it may differ on other machines.",
      "pos": [
        14223,
        14364
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Example:",
      "pos": [
        14366,
        14374
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Instead of:",
      "pos": [
        14376,
        14387
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can write:",
      "pos": [
        14503,
        14517
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource implementation does not contain user information",
      "pos": [
        14620,
        14677
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure there are no email names, account information, or names of people in the code.",
      "pos": [
        14681,
        14769
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource was tested with valid/invalid credentials",
      "pos": [
        14773,
        14823
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If your resource takes a credential as parameter:",
      "pos": [
        14827,
        14876
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Verify the resource works when Local System (or the computer account for remote resources) does not have access.",
      "pos": [
